The paper discusses the increasing importance of networking applications in the context of the Internet of Things (IoT), which suggests a focus on networking and communication technologies (cs.NI). The proposed interaction oriented architecture is based on a reference model of interaction semantics, which involves the design of software layers and components, suggesting a focus on software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the autonomy of technical systems and the need to understand the nature of semantics in interaction networks, which suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC) and systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions a data type model, which suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.DL).
